We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately to the Auditor the monthly accounts and financial reports for the months of October, November and December 2019.  Henceforth, he shall submit the accounts and financial reports to the Auditor on or before the prescribed deadline;

Instruct the concerned Accountable Officers (AOs) to prepare and submit their reports to the Municipal Treasurer on or before the third day of the ensuing month who shall, thereafter, submit to the MAO for recording all the DVs and payrolls, official receipts, including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the fifth day of the ensuing month;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to strictly comply with the timelines on the recording and submission of accounts to the Auditor, which is within the first ten (10) days of the ensuing month;

Look into the possibility of augmenting the MAO with personnel from other departments, especially during report preparation periods and/or allowing them to render overtime, subject to availability of funds, in order to submit the accounts and financial reports on the mandated deadlines; and

Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

