We recommended that the LCE request the MSWDO to revisit the Omnibus Guidelines and to:
Provide the Audit Team with the approved Project Proposal and masterlist of beneficiaries of the SFP;
Formulate  profiling  and  data  banking  of  children  as  required  under DSWD AO No.8;
Attach Approved Estimated Expenses for the CA; and
Attach the following documents in the liquidation of the CAs for SFP:
Attendance sheet (per day) listing the beneficiaries of the SFP and the presence of the parents signifying coordination and support;
Menu for the day;
Liquidation of expenses with Official Receipts; and
Evaluation Report on the Nutritional Status of the children
We also recommended that Management open a bank account solely for the transfer of funds for the DSWD Supplementary Feeding Program as required under the Omnibus Guidelines.

We recommended that Management:
Require the concerned Disbursing/Accountable Officers to submit  the accounts and financial reports to the Treasurer and thereafter to submit to the Accounting Office all the disbursement vouchers and payrolls, official receipts, including the corresponding reports of each month on or before the fifth day of the ensuing month or pursuant to the abovementioned pertinent provisions of laws, rules and regulations, as applicable;
