With the retirement of the designated OIC-MA, to appoint qualified personnel in the Accounting Unit to perform the duties and functions in the Department to be able to generate accounting reports and be able  to submit said reports on time; and
Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

(4) The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to reconcile their records on RPT and SET Receivables and make the necessary adjustments on the discrepancies so that a reliable Receivable account would be reflected in the financial statements;

(5) The Municipal Assessor to furnish the Municipal Treasurer with the copy of the updated/revised Tax Rolls of the Municipality, to come up with the required certified list for the RPT and SET Receivables; and

(6) The Municipal Treasurer to fumish the Municipal Accountant with duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year, to provide basis in setting up the Receivables at the beginning of the year, thereby ensuring that the requitement of —the provisions of Section 20, NGAS, Volume 1 for LGUs are met.

We recommended that Management establish or formulate specific guidelines and policies in the granting of all kinds of financial assistance to its constituents which may include, among others, the following:

1. Qualifications of the recipients, to include income levels which may be determined by the Municipal Social Welfare and Development Office (MSWDO) for all kinds of financial assistance;

2. For medical ailments, categorize criteria formulated and followed in granting assistance;

. Maximum and reasonable amount of financial assistance for each category;

. Frequency or maximum number of entitlements in a year;

. Mode of payment;

. Uniform authorization and documentary requirements such as Certificate of indigency from the barangay Captain, Social Worker Case Study, official Receipts, hospitals bills and other basic requirements to establish validity and correctness of the claims.

